===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|choppen|lang=enm}}, variant of {{term|chappen||to chop|lang=enm}}. Akin to {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|kappen||to chop, cut, hew|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|koppen||to cut off, lop, poll|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|kappe||to cut, lop off, poll|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|kapa||to cut|lang=sv}}, Albanian {{term|copë||piece, chunk|lang=sq}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{recons|cippian|lang=ang}} (only attested in compounds). More at {{l|en|chip}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
[[Image:Chopping garlic-01.jpg|thumb|Chopping garlic]]

# A cut of meat, often containing a section of a [[rib]].
#: {{usex|I only like lamb '''chops''' with mint jelly.}}
# A blow with an [[axe]], [[cleaver]], or similar [[utensil]].
#: {{usex|It should take just one good '''''chop''''' to fell the sapling.}}
# {{martial arts}} A blow delivered with the [[hand]] rigid and outstretched.
#: {{usex|A karate '''chop'''.}}
# [[ocean|Ocean]] [[wave]]s, generally caused by [[wind]], [[distinguished]] from [[swell]] by being smaller and not lasting as long.
# {{poker}} A hand where two or more players have an equal-valued hand, resulting in the chips being shared equally between them.
#: {{usex|With both players having an ace-high straight, the pot was a '''chop'''.}}
# {{informal|with "the"}} Termination, especially from employment.

